field.value:
If I want to override a built in helper for use in my view I can do the following:
[Helper(typeof(MyCustomFormHelper), "FormHelper")] public class HomeController : Controller { ... }
This works, replacing the built in FormHelper with my own.
However, the following will not work:
[Helper(typeof(MyCustomFormHelper), "Form")] public class HomeController : Controller { ... }
If I access "Form" in my view, then I will still receive a reference to the builtin FormHelper. The attached patch addresses this by checking that the prefix is not already in use.
